node.title: Pat Cummins ruled out of second Ashes Test after COVID-19 scare
node.alt: An Australian bowler pumps his fist as he runs near an England batter in the first men's Ashes Test at the Gabba.
node.description: Australian Test skipper Pat CumminsÂ has been ruled out of today's second Ashes Test. Cummins was a close contact of a COVID-positive diner at an Adelaide restaurant last night.
node.content: ["Australia captain Pat Cummins\u00a0has been ruled out of today's second Ashes Test.", "Cummins was a close contact of a COVID-positive diner at an Adelaide restaurant last night.", "Cummins has tested negative, but is required to isolate for seven days under South Australian health regulations.", "More to come."]
